  <original-body>When rendering textile inside a view using the textilize helper method, it is impossible to pass options to the rendered, which could be very useful if you want to filter HTML or perhaps just want to use `lite_mode`.

This proposed patch gives the ability to pass options by supplying them after the string like this
@@@ ruby
textilize(&quot;This is worded &lt;strong&gt;strongly&lt;/strong&gt;&quot;)
# =&gt; &quot;&lt;p&gt;This is worded &lt;strong&gt;strongly&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&quot;

textilize(&quot;This is worded &lt;strong&gt;strongly&lt;/strong&gt;&quot;, :filter_html)
# =&gt; &quot;&lt;p&gt;This is worded &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;strongly&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;&quot;
@@@</original-body>
